# This repository

- **Stack**: Payload 3, Next.js (App Router), Cloudflare D1 + R2 via `@payloadcms/db-d1-sqlite`, `@payloadcms/storage-r2`, OpenNext (`@opennextjs/cloudflare`).
- **Package manager**: `pnpm` only (see `package.json` engines).
- **Config**: `src/payload.config.ts` (`@payload-config` alias). Collections live in `src/collections/`.
- **Types**: After schema or plugin changes, run `pnpm run generate:types` (and `pnpm run generate:importmap` when admin UI/import map changes).
- **Migrations**: `src/migrations/`; new tables/columns need a migration and `pnpm payload migrate` (or your deploy pipeline’s migrate step). Use a real `PAYLOAD_SECRET` for local CLI migrate if required. **Site FK drift**: if inserts into `pages`/`articles` fail with `FOREIGN KEY` despite valid `site_id`, check `PRAGMA foreign_key_list(…)` — `site_id` must reference `sites`, not `sites_mig_old_20260629`. See [.cursor/docs/d1-site-id-fk-backup-table-sites.md](.cursor/docs/d1-site-id-fk-backup-table-sites.md).
- **When adding a new collection**: extend `payload_locked_documents_rels` in the same migration (FK column per collection); otherwise Admin document views can break with a blank main panel. See [docs/payload-d1-admin-troubleshooting.md](docs/payload-d1-admin-troubleshooting.md).
- **Multi-tenant**: `@payloadcms/plugin-multi-tenant` is enabled; `Config['user']` may be a **union** (e.g. `User` and MCP API keys)—narrow with `user.collection === 'users'` before assuming admin user fields like `roles` or `email`.
- **Super admin**: `src/utilities/superAdmin.ts`; optional env `PAYLOAD_SUPER_ADMIN_EMAILS` (comma-separated).
- **Do not** edit generated admin files under `src/app/(payload)/` that Payload marks as auto-generated unless you know the workflow.
- **Public `/` routing**: Middleware redirects `/` → `/en` on every host except `localhost`/`127.0.0.1`/`::1` (dev passthrough for `?site=`) and hosts listed in `PUBLIC_WELCOME_ROOT_HOSTS` (comma-separated). Put system gateway hosts like `sys.beginos.org` there so they keep `(welcome)`; custom `sites.primaryDomain` hosts should omit the list.

## Site layouts (`sites.siteLayout`)

- **Registry**: [`src/site-layouts/registry.ts`](src/site-layouts/registry.ts) maps each `SiteLayoutId` to a `Shell` component; [`src/app/[locale]/(frontend)/layout.tsx`](src/app/[locale]/(frontend)/layout.tsx) resolves document surface styles, wraps output in [`SiteLayoutErrorBoundary`](src/site-layouts/SiteLayoutErrorBoundary.tsx).
- **AMZ layout 1** (`amz-template-1`): implementation under [`src/site-layouts/amz-template-1/`](src/site-layouts/amz-template-1/) (chrome, theme, globals) with route components in [`pages/`](src/site-layouts/amz-template-1/pages). Single-column article layout.
- **AMZ layout 2** (`amz-template-2`): parallel directory [`src/site-layouts/amz-template-2/`](src/site-layouts/amz-template-2/) — targets structural parity with `amz-template-old` (e.g. article **3-column + TOC**, [`/[locale]/product/[asin]`](src/app/[locale]/(frontend)/product/[asin]/page.tsx) from Offers). Shares the same **Blueprint / `amzSiteConfigJson`** shape as layout 1.
- **Adding a new layout**: (1) Add `SiteLayoutId` in [`publicLandingTheme.ts`](src/utilities/publicLandingTheme.ts) if needed; (2) extend [`sites.siteLayout`](src/collections/Sites.ts) options / [`payload-types`](src/payload-types.ts) via migration + `pnpm run generate:types`; (3) add `src/site-layouts/<slug>/Shell.tsx` and register it in `registry.ts`; (4) if the shell needs root HTML/body classes, extend [`documentSurface.ts`](src/site-layouts/documentSurface.ts).

When suggesting commands, prefer existing scripts in `package.json` (`dev`, `build`, `test`, `lint`, `payload`, `deploy`).

## Commits (when writing PR/commit messages)

Use Conventional Commits: `feat|fix|chore|test|docs(scope): lowercase summary` (e.g. `fix(tests): align seed user with roles`).
